==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oven
<hw>Ov"en</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧v"'n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>ofen</ets>; akin to D. <ets>oven</ets>, OHG. <ets>ofan</ets>,
<ets>ovan</ets>, G. <ets>ofen</ets>, Icel. <ets>ofn</ets>, Dan.
<ets>ovn</ets>, Sw. <ets>ugn</ets>, Goth. <ets>a⟦uacute⟧hns</ets>, Gr.
<grk>'ipno`s</grk>, Skr. <ets>ukh⟦amac⟧</ets> pot.]</ety> <def>A place
arched over with brick or stonework, and used for baking, heating, or
drying; hence, any structure, whether fixed or portable, which may be
heated for baking, drying, etc.; esp., now, a chamber in a stove, used
for baking or roasting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

